Elastic block storage volume is a network drive attached to instances while they run.
allows instances to persist data even after termination.
CAN ONLY BE MOUNTED TO ONE INSTANCE AT A TIME.
SPECIFIC AZ.

1) not a physical drive. can be detached from an ec2 instance and attached to another one quickly.
2) two EBS Volumes attached to one instance.
USE CASE: preserve root volume when instance is terminated.


